---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How Podex collects, uses, and protects personal information">
  <main class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <article class="container max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-10 border-b border-border-subtle pb-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-accent">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl text-text">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: May 24, 2026</p>
      </header>
      <div class="space-y-9 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Overview</h2>
          <p>
            Podex indexes references discussed in podcasts and lets signed-in users save
            references, follow sources, and receive alerts. This policy explains personal
            information processed when you use the site or an account.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Information We Collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>Your email address when you request a passwordless sign-in link or maintain an account.</li>
            <li>Account choices such as saved references, followed sources, alert rules, and digest settings.</li>
            <li>Session and security data needed to authenticate you and prevent abuse.</li>
            <li>Basic request and diagnostic data needed to operate, secure, and improve the service.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">How We Use Information</h2>
          <p>
            We use personal information to provide account features, send requested sign-in
            links and notification digests, protect the service, respond to support or rights
            requests, and understand reliability of the product.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Sharing and Service Providers</h2>
          <p>
            Podex may use infrastructure, email delivery, analytics, transcription, and
            enrichment providers to run the service. They receive only information needed for
            their function and are expected to process it on our instructions or under their
            own disclosed terms. We do not sell personal information.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Retention and Choices</h2>
          <p>
            Account data is retained while your account is active and as needed for security,
            legal compliance, and reliable operations. You can disable digest email from
            account settings. You may request account access, correction, or deletion by
            contacting us.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Podcast Content and Rights Requests</h2>
          <p>
            Podex publishes structured references and short provenance context drawn from
            source material. Creators and rights holders may request review, correction,
            suppression, or takedown through our rights-request process.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about privacy or data rights can be sent to
            <a class="ml-1 text-accent hover:underline" href="mailto:privacy@podex.app">privacy@podex.app</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
